## 3. Post-Quantum Cryptography

### 3.1 Algorithm Choices

[Full section ~1800 words with tables]

| Component | Algorithm | Key Size | Sig Size | Standard |
| --- | --- | --- |
| Signatures | Dilithium3 | 1952 B | 3293 B | FIPS 204 |
| Key Exchange | Kyber768 | 1184 B | 1088 B | FIPS 203 |
| Hashing | SHA3-256 | 32 B | N/A | FIPS 202 |
| VRF | Dilithium-VRF | 1952 B | 3293 B | IRTF Draft |

**Trade-off**: 10x larger than ECDSA. Block sizes increase 5x. This is the cost of quantum safety.
We accept it.

### 3.2 Address Format

`qtc1q...` = bech32m(Dilithium-PK-Hash)
No backwards compatibility. No "1..." Bitcoin-style addresses. Clean break.

### 3.3 Quantum Threat Timeline

[Full section ~800 words citing NIST IR 8547, NSA CNSA 2.0]

2030: 50% chance of cryptographically relevant quantum computer.
2035: Mandated PQC for US government. 
QTC launches PQC-native to avoid migration debt.

---

## 4. Network & State Design

### 4.1 Mobile Networking Constraints

[Full section ~2000 words]

**Block Propagation**: 500KB max block. At 3G (1 Mbps), takes 4s. Tight but feasible.
**Gossipsub**: v1.1 with IHAVE/IWANT. Aggressive peer pruning. Target 8 peers.
**NAT Traversal**: libp2p AutoNAT + Circuit Relay v2. 
**State Expiry**: Accounts unused for 1 year expire. Must be refreshed. Keeps state <5GB on phone.

### 4.2 Light Clients

[Full section ~1200 words]

Recursive STARKs compress 1000-block history to 200KB proof. Phone verifies consensus without 
downloading headers. Enables trustless mobile wallets.

### 4.3 Execution Layer

[Full section ~1500 words]

**VM**: RISC-V 32-bit. Chosen for zkVM compatibility. Launch scope: transfers only.
**Gas**: EIP-1559. Base fee burned. Target 50% block fullness.
**Precompiles**: Dilithium verify, SHA3, VRF verify.

---

## 5. Tokenomics

### 5.1 Supply & Emission

[Full section ~1000 words with charts in text]

- **Max Supply**: 1,000,000,000 QTC. Fixed.
- **Genesis**: 0 QTC. Fair launch.
- **Emission**: 50 QTC/block initially. Halves every 4 years.
- **Year 1**: 525,600 blocks * 50 = 26.28M QTC (2.6% of cap)
- **Tail Emission**: After year 20, 0.5 QTC/block forever for security.

### 5.2 Fee Burn

EIP-1559 base fee is burned. If demand > emission, QTC is deflationary. 
Simulation pending in ECONOMIC_SIM.md. No promises.

### 5.3 Staking & Slashing

**Minimum Stake**: 100 QTC to prevent dust spam.  
**Slashing**: 10% for invalid PoUW. 100% for double-sign. No slashing for downtime.  
**Unbonding**: 21 days.

---

## 6. Governance

### 6.1 Phases

[Full section ~1200 words]

**Phase 0 - Benevolent Dictator**: Foundation controls upgrades until testnet.
**Phase 1 - On-Chain Voting**: 1 QTC = 1 vote. 30% quorum. 7 day voting.
**Phase 2 - Constitutional**: On-chain constitution ratified. Hard fork only for upgrades.

### 6.2 Governance Risks

Bribery, plutocracy, voter apathy. See THREAT_MODEL.md Attacks #52-#58. 
Mitigations under research. See future GOVERNANCE.md.

